# Patch 0004 — Per-workspace extension set (Kavacha Workspace Identities, Phase 2).
#
# What: adds an optional `extensions` field (array of addon IDs) to Zen's
# space object. Spaces with a list have exactly those extensions active;
# switching spaces enables/disables addons to match. Absent = all extensions
# (Zen behavior). A "Workspace Extensions" checkbox submenu in the space
# actions menu edits the set (first toggle seeds the list from everything
# currently active).
# Safety semantics: Firefox has no per-container extension scoping, so this
# toggles addons globally at switch time. The pref
# kavacha.workspaces.extensions-disabled tracks which addons *Kavacha*
# disabled — a space without a list re-enables only those, never overriding
# an addon the user disabled globally themselves. Applies are serialized so
# rapid space cycling cannot interleave, and toggle timing is logged (with
# zen.workspaces.debug) to evaluate switch latency.
# Status: ADR 0003 prototype — the riskiest Workspace Identities assumption.
# Ships behind normal defaults (no list = no behavior change).
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl.
# Applies on top of 0003 (same files).
